der Campbell, the early Restoration Movement leader who stressed as paramount the reliance on few essentials as well as what item?', 'reasoning': "The context mentions that The Living Oracles is a translation of the New Testament compiled and edited by Alexander Campbell. It also states that Campbell was a leader of the Restoration Movement, which stressed reliance on scripture and few essentials. The question asks for the item that, along with reliance on few essentials, was paramount in Campbell's teachings. The context does not explicitly mention another item, but it can be inferred that the item being referred to is scripture, as it is a key component of Campbell's teachings.", 'search_query': "What was paramount in Alexander Campbell's teachings besides reliance on few essentials?"}) (input_keys=None), Example({'augmented': True, 'context': ['Relax Your Mind (song) | "Relax Your Mind" featuring Faith Evans, is the second single by R&B vocal group Boyz II Men from the album "Full Circle". This was the last single that included bass singer, Michael McCary.', "Relax Your Mind (album) | Relax Your Mind is the debut, and only, album by the folk duo Jon & Alun who five years later founded the short-lived late-1960s English rock band Sweet Thursday. Jon Mark is best known for his records with Marianne Faithfull, John Mayall and Mark-Almond. Alun Davies became Cat Stevens's guitarist.", 'Tranquila | "Tranquila" (English: "Relax" ) is a song by Colombian singer J Balvin, and included in his debut studio album "La Familia" (2013). It was released as the second single of the album on December 11, 2012.'], 'question': "The person who's last single was Relax Your Mind has what nationality?", 'reasoning': 'The context mentions that "Relax Your Mind" is a song by the R&B vocal group Boyz II Men, and it is stated that this was the last single that included bass singer, Michael McCary. Therefore, we need to find out the nationality of Michael McCary.', 'search_query': 'What is 